# Problem 2 – Print Duplicate Elements

### Code

```python
a = [10,20,30,20,40,10,50]

seen = []

for i in a:
    if a.count(i) > 1 and i not in seen:
        print(i)
        seen.append(i)
```

### Output

```
10
20
```

### Logic

- Check whether an element appears more than once.
- Print it only if it has not been printed before.

