# Problem 9 – Left Rotate List by One Position

### Code

```python
a = [10,20,30,40,50]

first = a[0]

for i in range(len(a)-1):
    a[i] = a[i+1]

a[len(a)-1] = first

print(a)
```

### Output

```
[20,30,40,50,10]
```

### Logic

- Store the first element.
- Shift every element one position to the left.
- Place the first element at the end.

---

# Problem 10 – Right Rotate List by One Position

### Code

```python
a = [10,20,30,40,50]

last = a[-1]

for i in range(len(a)-1,0,-1):
    a[i] = a[i-1]

a[0] = last

print(a)
```

### Output

```
[50,10,20,30,40]
```

### Logic

- Store the last element.
- Shift every element one position to the right.
- Place the last element at the beginning.

